  "prompt": "What are the legal definitions of money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by hiding its true origin through a series of transactions. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Legal definitions typically involve three stages:\n- Placement (introducing illegal funds into financial system)\n- Layering (concealing source through complex transactions)\n- Integration (making funds appear legitimate)\n\n2. Common legal criteria include:\n- Knowingly concealing source of illegally obtained funds\n- Attempting to disguise origin of criminal proceeds\n- Transforming cash or assets derived from criminal activity\n- Engaging in financial transactions to hide illegal source\n\n3. Jurisdictional variations exist, but most definitions cover:\n- Financial transactions involving proceeds from criminal activity\n- Intent to disguise or legitimize illegal funds\n- Transferring or converting assets to hide criminal origin\n\n4. Typical predicate crimes include:\n- Drug trafficking\n- Fraud\n- Illegal gambling\n- Corruption\n- Tax evasion\n\n5. Penalties often involve:\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential criminal prosecution\n- Asset seizure\n- Imprisonment\n\nThese are general legal concepts. Specific definitions vary by jurisdiction and legal system.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any specific aspect of money laundering definitions?",
